-- African Mobile-Phone Services May Grow 20% by 2014, Business Day Reports
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-12-06T05:02:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/african-mobile-phone-services-may-grow-20-by-2014-business-day-reports.html
Value-added mobile-phone services may
grow 20 percent over the next five years and generate revenue of
more than $11.5 billion by 2014, Business Day reported, citing a
study by Informa Telecoms & Media.  Value-added services include mobile banking, Internet and
entertainment, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  